{"text":"<div role='navigation' class='navbox' aria-labelledby='Second_Punic_War' style='margin:0;float:right;clear:right;width:315px;margin-bottom:0.5em;margin-left:1em;;padding:3px'><table class='nowraplinks collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner' style='border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit'><tr><th scope='col' class='navbox-title' colspan='2' style='background-color:#B0C4DE;'><div class='plainlinks hlist navbar mini'><ul><li class='nv-view'><a href='/wiki/Template:Campaignbox_Second_Punic_War' title='Template:Campaignbox Second Punic War'><abbr title='View this template' style=';background-color:#B0C4DE;;background:none transparent;border:none;'>v</abbr></a></li><li class='nv-talk'><a href='/wiki/Template_talk:Campaignbox_Second_Punic_War' title='Template talk:Campaignbox Second Punic War'><abbr title='Discuss this template' style=';background-color:#B0C4DE;;background:none transparent;border:none;'>t</abbr></a></li><li class='nv-edit'><a class='external text' href='//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Campaignbox_Second_Punic_War&amp;action=edit'><abbr title='Edit this template' style=';background-color:#B0C4DE;;background:none transparent;border:none;'>e</abbr></a></li></ul></div><div id='Second_Punic_War' style='font-size:114%;margin:0 4em'><span style='line-height:1.6em'><a href='/wiki/Second_Punic_War' title='Second Punic War'><span class='wrap'>Second Punic War</span></a></span></div></th></tr><tr style='height:2px'><td colspan='2'></td></tr><tr><td colspan='2' class='navbox-list navbox-odd hlist' style='width:100%;padding:0px'><div style='padding:0em 0.25em'><dl><dt>Prelude</dt></dl><ul><li><a href='/wiki/Siege_of_Saguntum' title='Siege of Saguntum'>Saguntum</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Rhone_Crossing' title='Battle of Rhone Crossing'>Rhone</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Hannibal%27s_crossing_of_the_Alps' title='Hannibal's crossing of the Alps'>Crossing of the Alps</a></li></ul><dl><dt>Hannibal's invasion of Italy</dt></dl><ul><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Ticinus' title='Battle of Ticinus'>Ticinus</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_the_Trebia' title='Battle of the Trebia'>Trebia</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Lake_Trasimene' title='Battle of Lake Trasimene'>Lake Trasimene</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Ager_Falernus' title='Battle of Ager Falernus'>Ager Falernus</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Geronium' title='Battle of Geronium'>Geronium</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Cannae' title='Battle of Cannae'>Cannae</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Nola_(216_BC)' title='Battle of Nola (216 BC)'>1st Nola</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Nola_(215_BC)' title='Battle of Nola (215 BC)'>2nd Nola</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Nola_(214_BC)' title='Battle of Nola (214 BC)'>3rd Nola</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Beneventum_(214_BC)' title='Battle of Beneventum (214 BC)'>1st Beneventum</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Tarentum_(212_BC)' title='Battle of Tarentum (212 BC)'>1st Tarentum</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Capua_(212_BC)' class='mw-redirect' title='Battle of Capua (212 BC)'>1st Capua</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_the_Silarus' title='Battle of the Silarus'>Silarus</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Herdonia_(212_BC)' title='Battle of Herdonia (212 BC)'>1st Herdonia</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Beneventum_(212_BC)' title='Battle of Beneventum (212 BC)'>2nd Beneventum</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Capua_(211_BC)' title='Battle of Capua (211 BC)'>2nd Capua</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Herdonia_(210_BC)' title='Battle of Herdonia (210 BC)'>2nd Herdonia</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Numistro' title='Battle of Numistro'>Numistro</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Canusium' title='Battle of Canusium'>Battle of Canusium</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Tarentum_(209_BC)' title='Battle of Tarentum (209 BC)'>2nd Tarentum</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Grumentum' title='Battle of Grumentum'>Grumentum</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_the_Metaurus' title='Battle of the Metaurus'>Metaurus</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Crotona' title='Battle of Crotona'>Crotona</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Po_Valley_Raid' class='mw-redirect' title='Po Valley Raid'>Po Valley</a></li></ul><dl><dt>Roman expeditions to Iberia</dt></dl><ul><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Cissa' title='Battle of Cissa'>Cissa</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Ebro_River' title='Battle of Ebro River'>Ebro River</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Dertosa' title='Battle of Dertosa'>Dertosa</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_the_Upper_Baetis' title='Battle of the Upper Baetis'>Upper Baetis</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Cartagena_(209_BC)' title='Battle of Cartagena (209 BC)'>1st New Carthage</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Baecula' title='Battle of Baecula'>Baecula</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Ilipa' title='Battle of Ilipa'>Ilipa</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_the_Guadalquivir_(206_BC)' title='Battle of the Guadalquivir (206 BC)'>Guadalquivir</a></li></ul><dl><dt>Campaigns in Sicily and the western Mediterranean</dt></dl><ul><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Cornus' class='mw-redirect' title='Battle of Cornus'>Cornus</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Siege_of_Syracuse_(214%E2%80%93212_BC)' title='Siege of Syracuse (214–212 BC)'>Syracuse</a></li></ul><dl><dt>Roman invasion of Northeast Africa</dt></dl><ul><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Utica_(203_BC)' title='Battle of Utica (203 BC)'>Utica</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_the_Great_Plains' title='Battle of the Great Plains'>Great Plains</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Cirta' title='Battle of Cirta'>Cirta</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Zama' title='Battle of Zama'>Zama</a></li></ul><dl><dt>Naval battles</dt></dl><ul><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Lilybaeum' title='Battle of Lilybaeum'>Lilybaeum</a></li><li><a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Carteia' title='Battle of Carteia'>Carteia</a></li></ul></div></td></tr></table></div><p><b>Hasdrubal the Bald</b> was a <a href='/wiki/Carthaginian' class='mw-redirect' title='Carthaginian'>Carthaginian</a> general in the <a href='/wiki/Second_Punic_War' title='Second Punic War'>Second Punic War</a>. In 215 BCE, Hasdrubal was sent by Carthage to take the restive Roman territory of <a href='/wiki/Sardinia' title='Sardinia'>Sardinia</a>, but his fleet was wrecked en route in a storm off the <a href='/wiki/Balearic_Islands' title='Balearic Islands'>Balearic Islands</a>.<sup id='cite_ref-1' class='reference'><a href='#cite_note-1'>[1]</a></sup><sup id='cite_ref-2' class='reference'><a href='#cite_note-2'>[2]</a></sup> By the time he regrouped and arrived, <a href='/wiki/Titus_Manlius_Torquatus_(dictator)' title='Titus Manlius Torquatus (dictator)'>Manlius Torquatus</a> had largely pacified the territory, defeating <a href='/w/index.php?title=Hiostus&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1' class='new' title='Hiostus (page does not exist)'>Hiostus</a>, son of the Sardinian leader <a href='/wiki/Hampsicora' title='Hampsicora'>Hampsicora</a>, and was well-prepared against Hasdrubal's arrival. Manlius handily defeated the combined Carthaginian and Sardinian forces in the <a href='/wiki/Battle_of_Decimomannu' title='Battle of Decimomannu'>Battle of Decimomannu</a>, in which Hasdrubal the Bald was captured.</p><h2><span class='mw-headline' id='References'>References</span><span class='mw-editsection'><span class='mw-editsection-bracket'>[</span><a href='/w/index.php?title=Hasdrubal_the_Bald&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1' title='Edit section: References'>edit</a><span class='mw-editsection-bracket'>]</span></span></h2><div class='reflist' style='list-style-type: decimal;'><ol class='references'><li id='cite_note-1'><span class='mw-cite-backlink'><b><a href='#cite_ref-1'>^</a></b></span> <span class='reference-text'><a href='/wiki/Livy' title='Livy'>Livy</a>. <i><a href='/wiki/Ab_Urbe_Condita_Libri_(Livy)' title='Ab Urbe Condita Libri (Livy)'>The History of Rome by Titus Livius</a>: Books Nine to Twenty-Six</i>, trans. D. Spillan and Cyrus Edmonds. York Street, Covent Garden, London: Henry G. Bohn, 1868. <a rel='nofollow' class='external text' href='http://www.gutenberg.org/files/10907/10907-h/10907-h.htm#e34'>23.34</a></span></li><li id='cite_note-2'><span class='mw-cite-backlink'><b><a href='#cite_ref-2'>^</a></b></span> <span class='reference-text'><cite class='citation book'>Astin, A.E. (ed.). <a rel='nofollow' class='external text' href='http://books.google.ca/books?id=5Oe1u1H_OSMC&amp;pg=PA62&amp;lpg=PA62'><i>The Cambridge Ancient History, Volume 8: Rome and the Mediterranean to 133 B.C.</i></a> (2nd ed.). Cambridge University Press. p.&#160;62.</cite><span title='ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHasdrubal+the+Bald&amp;rft.btitle=The+Cambridge+Ancient+History%2C+Volume+8%3A+Rome+and+the+Mediterranean+to+133+B.C.&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.ca%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D5Oe1u1H_OSMC%26pg%3DPA62%26lpg%3DPA62&amp;rft.pages=62&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook' class='Z3988'><span style='display:none;'>&#160;</span></span></span></li></ol></div><!-- NewPP limit reportParsed by mw1255Cached time: 20170506150810Cache expiry: 2592000Dynamic content: falseCPU time usage: 0.048 secondsReal time usage: 0.073 secondsPreprocessor visited node count: 158/1000000Preprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000Post‐expand include size: 14842/2097152 bytesTemplate argument size: 2078/2097152 bytesHighest expansion depth: 9/40Expensive parser function count: 0/500Lua time usage: 0.020/10.000 secondsLua memory usage: 1.32 MB/50 MB--><!--Transclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)100.00%   60.043      1 -total 53.02%   31.834      1 Template:Reflist 47.26%   28.374      1 Template:Cite_book 44.40%   26.656      1 Template:Campaignbox_Second_Punic_War 41.70%   25.040      1 Template:Campaignbox 39.27%   23.578      1 Template